
Overview of verb lessen

The verb lessen has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (5) decrease, diminish, lessen, fall -- (decrease in size, extent, or range; "The amount of homework decreased towards the end of the semester"; "The cabin pressure fell dramatically"; "her weight fell to under a hundred pounds"; "his voice fell to a whisper")
2. (2) decrease, lessen, minify -- (make smaller; "He decreased his staff")
3. (1) subside, lessen -- (wear off or die down; "The pain subsided")
